 Research Simple Fixes or Mitigations:

Below are common examples of issues typically found and how to fix them:

Vulnerability                         	Severity	                     Suggested Fix
OpenSSH outdated version	                High	                   Update to the latest version of OpenSSH using your OS package manager.
SMBv1 Enabled              	              Critical                    	Disable SMBv1 protocol in Windows Features or via group policy.
Outdated browser or plugin (e.g., Flash)   	High	                  Uninstall or update to the latest secure version.
Weak TLS/SSL cipher suites	                Medium	                Disable weak ciphers in web server configuration (Apache, Nginx, etc.).
Missing Security Updates	                 High                   	Run apt update && apt upgrade (Linux) or Windows Update to patch immediately.
